cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with linguistic irregularity and proposes an information-theoretic measure of irregularity based on the predictability of forms in a language. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses a neural transduction model to estimate the irregularity measure. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with modeling linguistic structure and inflectional paradigms. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses a neural model to estimate the irregularity measure. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the sound patterns of irregular forms in languages.
